# Error Handling

## Rules

1. Every error must include a `code` field (machine-readable) and a `message`
   field (human-readable). Bare `Error("oops")` is rejected in review.
2. Errors cross layer boundaries as plain data — never throw across an
   interface boundary.
3. The outermost layer (UI / API handler) is responsible for translating
   internal errors into user-facing responses.
4. Use structured errors, not strings: `{ code: "USER_NOT_FOUND", message: ... }`.

## Pattern

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
throw new Error("user not found");

// ✅ Good
throw { code: "USER_NOT_FOUND", message: `No user with id ${id}`, retry: false };
```

